Photo by @amivitale. Fatu, one of the last northern white rhinos alive on the planet, nuzzles her keeper, James Mwenda, at Kenya’s Ol Pejeta Conservancy (@olpejeta). Fatu is the granddaughter of Sudan, the world’s last male northern white rhino who passed away in March due to age-related complications. The conservancy is fighting to save some of the world's most vulnerable creatures. Humans have brought the white rhino to the edge of extinction.

In honor of World Rhino Day on Sept. 22, I am sharing some of my favorite images of these magnificent, ancient creatures. Together we can work to save them - visit and support the communities that protect them.
